<br>
Yes Frank and Jim.  Cannon Fodder is truly a funny book.<br>
Its actually Phill's memorial to his brother Malcolm and recounts Malcolm's experiences.  Phill of course never served in Vietnam.<br><br>
It is a spoof of the &quot;I was a Lurp Rambo&quot; genre.<br><br>
Phill makes outrageous claims that it takes awhile for the reader to catch onto.  of course V-vets see it right away and non-vets might not.<br><br>
That is a real criticism of the book.<br><br>
Did you know that it is endorsed by General Westmoreland eventhough the author claims to have been involved in a plot to kill the General?<br><br>
No kidding . . .<br><br>
